I have installed several WINDOWS servers 2012 R2, 2016 and now 2019 servers with mod harbor.
With 100mbps up- and download you have a perfect internet server.
You really  need only to install XAMPP.
Then download the zip with the SLACK archives.
There Antonio explains exactly the steps to take when installing GIT and mod harbour.
I have notes of the installations and am in the process of creating instructions for ourselves. I think I can do that over the weekend and share it then.
You can get much more server speed it you update your HDD to a SSD.
We now use RDP and APACHE server on the same machine as standard for our software. RDP for FIVEWIN programs APACHE for web page, some php programs, TWEB and now for mod harbour.
High upload speed here is expensive. We reach 10-25 mbps. But all works fine.
